<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="W" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Well-spoken" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Well-spoken,</orth> speaking with grace, eloquent: <cit><quote>a knight w., neat and fine,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 1.2.10" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. I, 2, 10</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>these fair w. days,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 1.1.29" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 1, 29</bibl></cit>.* <cit><quote>Clarence is w.</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 1.3.348" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 3, 348</bibl></cit>. cf. <emph>better spoken</emph> in <bibl n="shak. lr 4.6.10" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. IV, 6, 10</bibl>, and <emph>fair-spoken.</emph>
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>